  "id": "phekb-bipolar-disorder-comprehensive",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "bipolar-disorder",
  "name": "Bipolar Disorder - Comprehensive Provider Query (Multi-Resource)",
  "description": "Provider-level query identifying bipolar patients via Condition + MedicationRequest. Path C captures patients on mood stabilizers without coded bipolar dx.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete bipolar disorder patient population. Some patients have a coded bipolar diagnosis. Others are on mood stabilizers (lithium, valproate, lamotrigine) without ever getting a formal bipolar diagnosis. Run multiple FHIR queries — diagnosis and mood stabilizer medications — and union the patient sets.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all bipolar patients.",
    "broad": "Find all bipolar disorder patients — by diagnosis or by mood stabilizer medications. Run multiple queries and union the patient sets.",
    "expert": "Run two queries. (1) Condition?code=http://snomed.info/sct|13746004 — bipolar dx. (2) MedicationRequest?code=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|6448,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|40254,http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|28439 — mood stabilizers. Union the patient IDs."
  },
